>   How to do Malise duty</span><hr size=1> I saw this mentioned earlier and I think alot of people don't quite understand all the techniques for malise duty that will maximize your mana.  First of all let's take the average level 51 mage who has 3 spells in the malise line.<br>
<br>
Malise<br>
60 mana 3 sec casting time<br>
-20 to resists<br>
<br>
Malisement<br>
100 mana 4 sec casting time<br>
-40 to resists<br>
<br>
Malosi<br>
175 mana 5 sec casting time<br>
-60 to resists<br>
<br>
All have a 6 second recast time<br>
<br>
Now if you will notice if you use the standard, atleast from what I hear from alot of malise line users, method which is chain cast malosi, you are in effect burning a hell of alot of mana 175 mana a pop, and when you consider that some mobs in hate take 10 casts to land malosi on (clerics, scorn banshees, etc) this is alot of mana, thus with any high pull rate you will be very low on mana and will not be able to mal some of them, same is true for shrooms in seb, etc.<br>
<br>
Now the preferred method on heavy resist mobs, is land malise, then malisement, then malosi.  If you fail at one step just repeat at that step until you succeed.  This method minimizes mana expense.  Let us take an example where you have a mob that would take 5 casts to get malosi on.  This would take 875 mana, and 49 seconds.  Now let us assume also that it would take 5 casts to get malise, then you would malisement, then malosi.  This would take 575 mana, and 48 seconds.<br>
<br>
So we have 300 less in mana cost but with similar seconds of casting time.  If time is not ultra essential (and in many cases it is essential but not this essential) this is the route you want to take, over time you will be spending alot less mana.<br>
<br>
If time is ultra essential then alternate malise /w malisement.  This means if malise fails, cast malisement instead of waiting for refresh of malise and vice versa.  Applied to the same situation above you get 3 casts of malise (3rd lands), 3 casts of malisement (3rd lands after malise hits), and 1 cast of malosi.  This costs 655 mana and takes 26 seconds.  This is still better than straight malosi in casting cost, and faster in terms of casting time for those ultra essential moments.<br>
<br>
One last note, these figures are slightly off because the resist rate of malise is higher than malisement which is higher than malosi, but even so this small resist penalty does not have a major affect in the long run.<br>
<br>
Also remember that on low MR mobs, this method is not necessary since you will land the majority of your first cast spells, however you might still want to consider using malisement over malosi in these situations if the extra -20 to resists will probably make little difference, since you can almost cast 2 malisements for every malosi.<br>
<br>
Xoran<br>
